subSubSection.paragraph:
Premaxilla with inner band of small villiform teeth and outer series of larger conical teeth; a few teeth of inner band near symphysis enlarged as posteriorly directed conical teeth; two teeth in outer series near symphysis enlarged, canine-like; symphysis toothless. Dentary with series of conical teeth, one enlarged into recurved canine at the first one-third on each side; anterior to recurved canine, band of villiform to small conical teeth extending to near symphysis where one canine-like tooth is enlarged, posteriorly directed and present only on jaw’s left side; symphysis toothless. Vomerine tooth patch grossly pentagonal, with a posterior prolongation of small teeth arranged in four pairs, which are followed by a series of six single teeth (
Fig. 3
); vomerine and palatine teeth villiform to small conical, those following the posterior part of vomerine patch somewhat enlarged and conical; palatine teeth in a band, narrowest posteriorly. Mesopterygoids with many villiform teeth. Tongue with a patch of minute teeth on upper bony blade, none at borders, tip, or ventral side. Gill rakers long, but those at center of lower first arch only somewhat longer than opposite gill filaments.
